    <summary>Command-line utility for complex IPv4 and IPv6 network calculations</summary>
    <description>
IPNetwork is a comprehensive command-line utility for handling complex network calculations involving IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, netmasks, CIDR notation, subnet operations, and supernetting.

## Features

- IPv4 and IPv6 support
- Network parsing with multiple CIDR guessing strategies (ClassFull, ClassLess, NetworkAware)
- Subnet and supernet calculations
- IP range to CIDR conversion
- Network containment and overlap detection
- IP address enumeration
- Unique Local Address (ULA) generation for IPv6
- Comprehensive command-line interface

## Usage

Display network information:
```
ipnetwork 10.0.0.0/8
```

Split network into subnets:
```
ipnetwork -s 9 10.0.0.0/8
```

Supernet networks:
```
ipnetwork -w 192.168.0.0/24 192.168.1.0/24
```

Test network containment:
```
ipnetwork -C 10.0.0.1 10.0.0.0/8
```

Test network overlap:
```
ipnetwork -o 10.0.0.1/24 10.0.0.0/8
```

For full usage instructions, run: `ipnetwork -h`

## Donate

If you find IPNetwork useful, consider supporting the project: https://github.com/lduchosal/ipnetwork/blob/master/DONATE.md
